The paper deals with the analysis of a large-scale location-based dataset, which is a common topic in the subfields of social informatics (cs.SI) and software development (cs.SD). The use of mobile phone data also suggests a potential fit with the subfield of cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the validation and uncertainty estimation of home detection algorithms, which could be relevant to the subfields of systems and control (cs.SY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
